at it had been designed to overcome. It explores the phantasmatic and absurd dimensions of the transformation of social reality under conditions of global capitalism, deconstructing the utopian fantasies of the state, and drawing attention to the eruption of insurgent utopias staged by those with nothing left to lose.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aEcuador-Politics and government-21st century. 0aPolitical science. 0aSustainable developmentzAmazon River Valley. 0aSustainable developmentzEcuador. 0aUtopiaszEcuador. 70(DE-588)4070873-10(DE-627)1060991240(DE-576)209182210aEntwicklungsplanung2gnd 70(DE-588)4070874-30(DE-627)1045486060(DE-576)209182229aEntwicklungsprojekt2gnd 70(DE-588)4133869-80(DE-627)1041164120(DE-576)209647493aMisserfolg2gnd 70(DE-588)4211061-00(DE-627)1050914720(DE-576)210201622aEntwicklungsmodell2gnd 7aHISTORY / Latin America / South America.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300262933?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262933423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300262933/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075408-7  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_Y